The paper proposes a mechanism design framework for spectrum auction with a focus on privacy preservation and social efficiency. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) or Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves designing allocation mechanisms with approximation factors, which could fall under the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of computation and communication overhead, which could be relevant to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a strategyproof auction mechanism, which could be related to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
